NEW FRANCUA LINGUA LANGUAGE

.fl -- Franca Lingua
    This programming language is inspired from the term "Francua Lingua", which means a language that unites many people of different ethnic backgrounds. The programming equivalent, as you would expect, derives from this term in computer science. Basically, it is a common programming language that unites people who code differently (C developers vs Python developers, for an example)



Francua Lingua is the term I will call it, as there is no official name for it. You can recommend one if you want.


int a = 5
int b = 10
exit(a + b)

